</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In September, a company called Digital=
 World Acquisition Corp. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/25945687.256650/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRh=
LzE4NDk2MzUvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIxMTEzNTQxL3RtMjEyNzAzNWQxXzQyNGI0Lmh0bQ/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cBa3e8cb2e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">went public</a>, raising <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25945687.256650/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc=
2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE4NDk2MzUvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIxMTE0MjY3L3Rt=
MjEyNzE4MmQxXzhrLmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdd9a0e0f" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">$287.5 mi=
llion</a> by selling stock to investors at $10 per share. DWAC=C2=A0is a sp=
ecial purpose acquisition company, or SPAC, a=C2=A0blind pool to find anoth=
er company to take public. The idea is that the SPAC puts the money it rais=
es into a bank account, finds a private company that wants to go public, an=
d merges with that target company. The target company gets the money in the=
 SPAC=E2=80=99s bank account=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0$287.5 million or so, in D=
WAC=E2=80=99s case =E2=80=94=C2=A0and the public shareholders of the SPAC g=
et back shares in the target company, which becomes a public company by mer=
ging with the SPAC. If the SPAC doesn=E2=80=99t find a deal within two year=
s, or if the shareholders don't like the deal it finds, they get their $10 =
back.[1]</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In October, DWAC <a href=3D"https:=
//link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25945687.256650/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2V=
jLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE4NDk2MzUvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIxMTI4MjMxL3RtMj=
EzMDcyNGQxX2V4OTktMS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc9cc5a5a" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">announ=
ced its merger</a>, and=C2=A0it was a doozy. The private company that DWAC =
will take public is Trump Media &amp; Technology Group, which is =E2=80=A6=
=C2=A0a =E2=80=A6=C2=A0media =E2=80=A6=C2=A0and =E2=80=A6=C2=A0technology =
=E2=80=A6=C2=A0group? =E2=80=A6=C2=A0affiliated with Donald Trump. Nobody h=
ad heard of TMTG before it announced its SPAC merger, and nobody has heard =
all that much about it since. =E2=80=9CTrump Media &amp; Technology Group (=
=E2=80=98TMTG=E2=80=99) will soon be launching a social network, named =E2=
=80=98TRUTH Social,=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D said the merger announcement, promisi=
ng a beta launch in November. It=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/25945687.256650/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAyMS8xMi8=
wMS90cnVtcC1zcGFjLXNvY2lhbC1tZWRpYS1jb21wYW55LWFwcGVhcnMtdG8tbWlzcy1maXJzdC=
1kZWFkbGluZS5odG1sP3V0bV90ZXJtPUF1dG9mZWVkJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09U29jaWFsJnV0bV9jb=
250ZW50PU1haW4mdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1Ud2l0dGVyI0VjaG9ib3g9MTYzODM4ODM0Mw/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cBc7bdcf80" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;">missed that deadline</a>. A test version =
of the site <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/259456=
87.256650/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud2FzaGluZ3RvbnBvc3QuY29tL3RlY2hub2xvZ3kvMjAyMS8xM=
C8yMS90cnVtcC10cnV0aC1zb2NpYWwtZmFrZS1hY2NvdW50cy8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
Ba2d5127e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">seemed to be</a> just a clone of open-source social netw=
ork Mastodon. TMTG=E2=80=99s website has a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/25945687.256650/aHR0cHM6Ly90bXRnY29ycC5jb20vY29tcG=
FueS1vdmVydmlldw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1023ea37" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=E2=80=9Ccompan=
y overview=E2=80=9D slide deck</a>=C2=A0that contains no business informati=
on=C2=A0and does not mention anyone involved in building its supposed techn=
ology.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CThis appears to be a shell company buying a shell comp=
any,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2594=
5687.256650/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXhpb3MuY29tL25ld3NsZXR0ZXJzL2F4aW9zLXByby1yYXR=
hLWI0NGIwYjA0LTllNDItNDA3My1hYTAxLTQyNGRlZDgxNTJlNS5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cB12ae4bb3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">wrote Dan Primack</a>.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25945687.2=
56650/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtM=
jEvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1kb25hbGQtdHJ1bXAtZG9lcy1hLXNwYWM_Y21w=
aWQ9QkJEMTIwNjIxX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3N=
sZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjExMjA2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8=
524a319a23cB656f01bb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> wrote at the time</a>:</p><blockquote><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If Donald Trump announced =E2=80=9Chey I=E2=80=99m g=
onna do a social media company, buy some stock,=E2=80=9D people would buy s=
ome stock. And then he=E2=80=99d get a lot of money. And then if the social=
 media platform did not end up being profitable =E2=80=94 as I cannot imagi=
ne it would be! =E2=80=94 then he would, uh, still have that money? And if =
the social media platform did not end up being <em>launched</em> =E2=80=94 =
if Trump and his crack team of technologists just couldn=E2=80=99t actually=
 build a well-functioning online social network =E2=80=94 then he would, uh=
, still have that money? And if there was no crack team of technologists at=
 all, if nobody even <em>tried</em> to build the social media platform =E2=
=80=94 then you see where I am going with this right?</p></blockquote><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway. The deal is that DWAC will put in the money=
 in its bank account =E2=80=94=C2=A0about $293 million =E2=80=94=C2=A0and g=
et about 37 million shares of TMTG[2]; the current owners of TMTG =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0presumably Donald Trump and =E2=80=A6=C2=A0some =E2=80=A6=C2=A0other =
people? =E2=80=94=C2=A0will get a variable number of shares that I am just =
going to call 125.8 million.[3] So roughly speaking Trump is selling about=
=C2=A023% of his company for $293 million.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
Before the merger was announced, DWAC=E2=80=99s stock traded publicly betwe=
en call it $9.92 and $9.97 per share. This is=C2=A0normal for a SPAC in lat=
e 2021: SPACs were hot in early 2021 but the trend faded, and these days a =
SPAC share=C2=A0pretty much represents the right to get back $10 at some in=
definite point in the next two years. The day after the merger was announce=
d, DWAC closed at $45.50. The next day, it closed at $94.20. It has not clo=
sed below $40 since. On Friday it closed at $44.97.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">This sounds good, but it is actually somewhat awkward for Tr=
ump and TMTG. <em>The price is too high.</em> Trump is selling about 23% of=
 his company for $293 million, but the public market says that that stake i=
s worth about $1.7 billion.[4]</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The public m=
arket, I should emphasize, is saying that based on=C2=A0<em>nothing</em>. A=
s of last Friday, there was=C2=A0absolutely no financial or technical or bu=
siness information about TMTG available to the public; so far there is almo=
st no sign that TMTG is actually building a social network or a streaming p=
latform or anything else.[5]</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the market=
 says that TMTG is worth $44.97 per share. And TMTG is selling stock =E2=80=
